  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct at Model Risk Level 5. This package follows the Morrison COU2 archetype and exercises the Complete-profile high-MRL pathway (NC-3). All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors are fully assessed at high rigor; each carries an inline AcceptanceCriteria object, explicit requiredLevel and achievedLevel integers, and a detailed rationale grounded in the structured evidence base. A documented sensitivity analysis (Sobol' second-order, n=8192 QMC samples) identifies cortical shell thickness and screw–rod interface friction as dominant variance contributors. The validation dataset spans N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories. Decision outcome is Accepted; one factor (Test conditions) achieved level equals required level with zero shortfall. Provenance is complete back to the Nagaraja et al. (2020) DOI.",
