      "rationale": "Validation activities use production hardware from the same lot as the commercial device (Lot 2023-A screws, Lot 2023-B rods). Loading scenario directly replicates ASTM F1717 compression-bending — the exact loading mode specified in the COU. Gap analysis (GAP-F1717-NC-v1.1): (1) Validation uses dry conditions; clinical use involves wet/saline environment — assessed as negligible QoI impact (<1%) based on literature data for Ti-6Al-4V in physiological saline. (2) Validation uses UHMWPE surrogate blocks; clinical use involves bone — acknowledged; surrogate blocks are the ASTM F1717 standard substrate and are used for all predicate comparisons. (3) Single loading direction tested; clinical loading is multi-axial — acknowledged as a standard limitation of F1717 methodology, consistent with predicate data. All gaps assessed as having negligible impact on the validation conclusion. Gradation 5 achieved: identical hardware, direct loading replication, and comprehensive gap analysis with quantified impact assessments."
